      <subpart id="DLM351434" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" toc="yes" act.no="74" act.type="public" date.as.at="2009-07-01" date.assent="2005-06-03" date.first.valid="2005-06-04" stage="reprint" year="2005">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
        <heading>Victims’ claims</heading>
        <crosshead id="DLM351435" toc="yes">Payment of money into account and information about filing claims</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM351436" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">17</label>
          <heading>Compensation of prisoners, etc, must be paid to Secretary</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person must pay to the Secretary, immediately, all money that, after the commencement of this Act, the person becomes liable to pay as compensation and—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in satisfaction of a final judgment of a court or tribunal on a specified claim made before <insertwords>1 July 2010</insertwords>; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>as, or as part of, an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim made before <insertwords>1 July 2010</insertwords>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>For the purposes of subsection (1)(a), a judgment of a court or tribunal (whether at first instance or on appeal) is final—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>when the time for filing appeals against the judgment expires and no appeals of that kind have been filed; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if appeals against the judgment may be brought or heard only by leave, when—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the time for applying for leave expires and no application for leave has been made; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>all applications for leave have been withdrawn or finally determined and declined; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>no party granted leave to appeal has, within the time for commencing an appeal, commenced an appeal; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>when all appeals against the judgment have been withdrawn or finally determined.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Nothing in subsection (1)(b) applies to an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim containing a provision to the effect that it is a settlement that is not subject to this subpart.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (1) applies even if that money is also—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>required to be paid to a creditor of the accused or the offender; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>liable to be attached or taken in execution at the instance of a creditor of the accused or the offender.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>In subsection (4), a <def-term id="DLM351437">creditor</def-term> includes the Commissioner of Inland Revenue or any other person or body to whom any taxes, duties, fines, levies, or other charges, deductions, or amounts (for example, under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305208" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Child Support Act 1991" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749779" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Child Support Act 1991</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="309797" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749779" atidlm:targetKey="1326632" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM253150" atidlm:targetName="Child Support Act 1991" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749779" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM253150.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351436" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305209" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Student Loan Scheme Act 1992" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749780" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Student Loan Scheme Act 1992</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="309798" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749780" atidlm:targetKey="1493294" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM286951" atidlm:targetName="Student Loan Scheme Act 1992" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749780" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM286951.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351436" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>) are payable.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>No person has a right of action against the Crown, an agent of the Crown, or any other person, in respect of any investment or payment of money permitted or required by this subpart or by regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305210" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749781" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310120" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749781" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749781" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351436" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM351438"><amended-provision>Section 17(1)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation> (with effect from 30 June 2007), on <amendment-date>31 July 2007</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305211" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 5" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749782" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 5</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310121" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749782" atidlm:targetKey="2568206" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM411470" atidlm:targetName="prov 5" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749782" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM411462.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351438" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Prisoners’ and Victims’ Claims Amendment Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 29).</history-note>
              <history-note id="DLM351439"><amended-provision>Section 17(1)(b)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation> (with effect from 30 June 2007), on <amendment-date>31 July 2007</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305212" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 5" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749783" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 5</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310122" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749783" atidlm:targetKey="2568206" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM411470" atidlm:targetName="prov 5" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749783" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM411462.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351439" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Prisoners’ and Victims’ Claims Amendment Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 29).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351440" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">18</label>
          <heading>Secretary deducts money for legal aid, reparation, and earlier orders, then pays surplus into account</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>On receiving money under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305213" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 17" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749784" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 17</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310123" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749784" atidlm:targetKey="2110806" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351436" atidlm:targetName="prov 17" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749784" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351440" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Secretary must, as soon as practicable,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>first, pay out of that money any sum necessary to satisfy fully any relevant charge—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>in favour of the Legal Services Agency; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>on proceeds of proceedings relating to the specified claim, and to which a grant of legal aid relates; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>arising by operation of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305214" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 32" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749785" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 32</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310124" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749785" atidlm:targetKey="372682" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM72205" atidlm:targetName="prov 32" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749785" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM71923.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351440" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Legal Services Act 2000</citation>; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>second, pay out of that money any sum necessary to satisfy fully any amounts of reparation owed by the accused or the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>third, pay out of that money any sum necessary to satisfy fully any amounts owed by the accused or the offender under any relevant order made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305216" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749787" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310126" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749787" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749787" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351440" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> following an earlier receipt of money under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305217" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 17" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749788" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 17</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310127" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749788" atidlm:targetKey="2110806" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351436" atidlm:targetName="prov 17" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749788" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351440" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>fourth, pay any surplus remaining into the account.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In this section,—</text>
                <def-para id="DLM351441">
                  <para>
                    <text><def-term id="DLM351442">amounts of reparation</def-term> means—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an amount due under a sentence of reparation imposed under—</text>
                        <label-para skeleton="no">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                          <para>
                            <text>the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305218" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Sentencing Act 2002" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749789" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Sentencing Act 2002</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310128" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749789" atidlm:targetKey="758400" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM135341" atidlm:targetName="Sentencing Act 2002" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749789" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM135341.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351441" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                        <label-para skeleton="no">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                          <para>
                            <text>the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305219" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Criminal Justice Act 1985" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749790" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Criminal Justice Act 1985</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310129" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749790" atidlm:targetKey="442200" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM76615" atidlm:targetName="Criminal Justice Act 1985" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749790" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM76615.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351441" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an amount due under an order of reparation</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </def-para>
                <def-para id="DLM351443">
                  <para>
                    <text><def-term id="DLM351444">order of reparation</def-term> means—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305220" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 106" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749791" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 106</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310130" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749791" atidlm:targetKey="770402" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM136807" atidlm:targetName="prov 106" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749791" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM136805.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351443" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link>, <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305221" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 108" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749792" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 108</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310131" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749792" atidlm:targetKey="770405" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM136810" atidlm:targetName="prov 108" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749792" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM136805.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351443" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link>, or <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305222" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 110" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749793" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 110</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310132" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749793" atidlm:targetKey="770409" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM136814" atidlm:targetName="prov 110" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749793" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM136805.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351443" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Sentencing Act 2002</citation>; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305224" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 84" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749795" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 84(1)(b)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310134" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749795" atidlm:targetKey="844064" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM150084" atidlm:targetName="prov 84" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749795" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM149452.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351443" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Children, Young Persons, and Their Families Act 1989</citation>; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305226" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 283" atidlm:xmlId="DLM749797" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 283(f) or (g)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310136" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM749797" atidlm:targetKey="851674" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM153436" atidlm:targetName="prov 283" atidlm:sourceName="DLM749797" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM152191.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351443" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Children, Young Persons, and Their Families Act 1989</citation>; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>an order that requires the payment of an amount to compensate, or to make restitution to, the victim of an offence against an enactment.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </def-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (1)(b) applies regardless of the conditions of a relevant sentence of reparation or order of reparation, for example, any conditions in respect of the following matters:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>whether the total amount of reparation to be paid is to be paid in 1 lump sum or in instalments:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if the amount is to be paid in 1 lump sum, whether it is to be paid immediately or at some specified future date:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if the amount is to be paid in instalments, the frequency and amounts of the instalments.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351445" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">19</label>
          <heading>Status of money paid to Secretary or into account</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Money paid into the account, or to the Secretary, in accordance with this subpart, may be paid out only in accordance with this subpart or regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305230" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750001" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310140" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750001" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750001" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351445" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In particular, until paid out to the accused or the offender in accordance with this subpart or regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305231" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750002" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310141" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750002" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750002" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351445" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, that money is, even if the accused or the offender has a beneficial interest in it,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>not available for the payment of a creditor of the accused or the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>not liable to be attached or taken in execution at the instance of a creditor of the accused or the offender.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>In subsection (2), a <def-term id="DLM351446">creditor</def-term> includes the Commissioner of Inland Revenue or any other person or body to whom any taxes, duties, fines, levies, or other charges, deductions, or amounts (for example, under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305233" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Child Support Act 1991" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750004" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Child Support Act 1991</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310143" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750004" atidlm:targetKey="1326632" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM253150" atidlm:targetName="Child Support Act 1991" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750004" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM253150.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351445" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305234" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Student Loan Scheme Act 1992" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750005" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Student Loan Scheme Act 1992</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310144" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750005" atidlm:targetKey="1493294" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM286951" atidlm:targetName="Student Loan Scheme Act 1992" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750005" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM286951.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351445" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>) are payable.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Money paid into the account, in accordance with this subpart, is money paid to the Crown in trust for the accused or the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>Nothing in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305235" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="part 7 Trust money" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750006" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Part 7</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310145" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750006" atidlm:targetKey="889807" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM162980" atidlm:targetName="part 7 Trust money" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750006" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM162980.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351445" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Public Finance Act 1989</citation> (which relates to trust money) applies to money that, in accordance with this section, is paid to the Crown in trust for the accused or the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351447" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">20</label>
          <heading>Secretary to give notice of payments into account, etc</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>After paying money into the account under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305237" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 18" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750008" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 18(1)(d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310147" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750008" atidlm:targetKey="2110811" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351440" atidlm:targetName="prov 18" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750008" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351447" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Secretary must as soon as practicable—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>give a written notice communicating—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the fact that compensation is required to be paid to the accused or the offender; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the fact that, under this subpart, the compensation must be paid to the Secretary and he or she must, after making certain deductions, pay any surplus remaining into the account; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the name and other identifying details of the accused or the offender; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iv</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the amount of money paid into the account; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">v</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the date on which the payment was made; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>explain in the notice that the money paid into the account must be held in trust for the accused or the offender until it is paid out in accordance with this subpart or regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305238" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750009" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310148" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750009" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750009" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351447" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>give in the notice general information about how victims of the person for whom money is required to be held in trust might file a victim’s claim under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305239" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750010" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310149" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750010" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750010" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351447" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> and within the deadline fixed by section 28(2)(c).</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section and <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305241" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750012" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 21</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310151" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750012" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750012" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351447" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> do not permit or require a written notice in respect of a matter to be given contrary to an enactment, rule of law, or order or direction of a court or tribunal prohibiting or forbidding the publication of—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any report or account of the whole or any part of proceedings (including, without limitation, the evidence adduced or the submissions made); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the name of any person, or any name or particulars likely to lead to the identification of that person; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the affairs of any person.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351448" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">21</label>
          <heading>How and to whom notice, etc, given</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305242" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750013" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310152" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750013" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750013" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351448" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> must be given—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>by being served on people—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>whom the Secretary reasonably believes may be or are victims of the accused or the offender; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>whose contact details are available to the Secretary; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>by being sent to the chief executive of each government department that the Secretary believes may have an interest in the matter.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305243" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750014" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310153" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750014" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750014" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351448" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is given under subsection (1) to the people to whom it is required to be given under that subsection, it may, if the Secretary thinks fit, also be given by 1 or more of the methods in subsection (4).</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>However, if the notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305246" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750017" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310156" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750017" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750017" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351448" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is not given under subsection (1) to all the people to whom it is required to be given under that subsection, it must be given by 1 or more of the methods in subsection (4).</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The methods referred to in subsections (2) and (3) are—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>publication in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>publication through a site on the Internet that is publicly accessible at all reasonable times; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>publication in daily newspapers published in Auckland, Hamilton, Wellington, Christchurch, and Dunedin.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary is not required by this section to give a person, by any method, the notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305251" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750022" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310162" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750022" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750022" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351448" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> if the Secretary believes on reasonable grounds that a limitation defence could be pleaded successfully in response to a victim’s claim made by that person.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must send the Secretary of the Tribunal a copy of every notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305252" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750023" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310163" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750023" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750023" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351448" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> and given in accordance with this section.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351449" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">22</label>
          <heading>Single process for 2 or more payments in same period</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>If a notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305253" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750024" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310164" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750024" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750024" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351449" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is to be given within 6 months after the sending date of any previous notice required by section 20 in respect of the same accused or offender, the notice must—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>be given as an addition to the previous notice; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>indicate that, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305255" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750026" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28(2)(c)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310166" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750026" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750026" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351449" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the deadline for filing victims’ claims under this subpart is the later of the following:</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the close of the day that is 6 months after the sending date of the previous notice; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the close of the day that is 2 months after the sending date of the notice.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351450" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">23</label>
          <heading>Sending date: what it means</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>In <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305256" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 22" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750027" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 22</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310167" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750027" atidlm:targetKey="2110816" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351449" atidlm:targetName="prov 22" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750027" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351450" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305257" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750028" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310168" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750028" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750028" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351450" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, <def-term id="DLM351451">sending date</def-term>, in relation to a notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305258" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750029" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310169" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750029" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750029" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351450" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> notifying a payment into the account, means whichever is the earlier of the following dates:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the date that is 2 months after the date of the payment; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the date on which the notice is first given in accordance with <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305259" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750030" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 21</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310170" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750030" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750030" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351450" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351452" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">24</label>
          <heading>Secretary’s duties for purposes of section 21</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must, for the purposes of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305261" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750032" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 21</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310172" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750032" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750032" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351452" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, take reasonable steps to identify, and ascertain the contact details of, people who may be or are victims of the accused or the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Those steps include requesting under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305262" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 33A" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750033" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 33A</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310173" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750033" atidlm:targetKey="881245" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM158509" atidlm:targetName="prov 33A" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750033" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM157891.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351452" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Victims’ Rights Act 2002</citation> the current address (including the full name) of a person—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>who may be or is a victim of the accused or the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>who asked for notice of certain matters under that Act and gave his or her current address for that purpose.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>To help to identify, and ascertain the contact details of, people who may be or are victims of the accused or the offender, the Secretary may, by making a request for the purpose to the appropriate Registrar or Judge Advocate General, and without paying a fee, access or search, inspect, and take or be issued with copies of or extracts from, court documents or records that—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <text>relate to criminal proceedings, proceedings of a disciplinary officer under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986637" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194805 - Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194854" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007837" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194854" atidlm:targetKey="2572255" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM401062" atidlm:targetName="Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194854" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM401062.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351452" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, or proceedings of the Court Martial; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>are or may be relevant to that purpose.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Those court documents or records include the ones specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305265" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750036" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35(2)(a) to (d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310176" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750036" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750036" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351452" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary is not required by this section to take steps to ascertain the contact details of a person if the Secretary believes on reasonable grounds that a limitation defence could be pleaded successfully in response to a victim’s claim made by that person.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194834"><amended-provision>Section 24(3)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986638" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194801 - prov 81" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194855" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 81</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007838" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194855" atidlm:targetKey="10327843" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1034362" atidlm:targetName="prov 81" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194855" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1034319.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194834" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Armed Forces Discipline Amendment Act (No 2) 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 98).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351453" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">25</label>
          <heading>Access to records of <insertwords>the Court Martial</insertwords> proceedings, etc, to identify, and ascertain contact details of, victims</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section applies to a document or record specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305266" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750037" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35(2)(c) or (d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310177" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750037" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750037" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351453" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, requested under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305268" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 24" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750039" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 24(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310179" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750039" atidlm:targetKey="2110819" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351452" atidlm:targetName="prov 24" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750039" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351453" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, and that the Judge Advocate General considers, and has advised the Secretary, should not be disclosed for reasons of security.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary cannot access or search, inspect, and take or be issued with copies or extracts from, the document or record.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Judge Advocate General may, if he or she thinks fit, perform the Secretary’s duties under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305269" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750040" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 20 to 24</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310180" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750040" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750040" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351453" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> so far as they relate to and arise from the document or record.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section overrides <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305270" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750041" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 20 to 24</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310181" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750041" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750041" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351453" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194835"><amended-provision>Section 25 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986639" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194817 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194856" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007840" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194856" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194856" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194835" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351454" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">26</label>
          <heading>Procedure if no victims of accused or offender</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must apply to a Tribunal for an order that all money held in the account for the accused or the offender be paid to the accused or the offender promptly if the Secretary—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>has, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305271" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 24" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750042" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 24</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310182" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750042" atidlm:targetKey="2110819" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351452" atidlm:targetName="prov 24" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750042" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351454" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, taken reasonable steps to identify, and ascertain the contact details of, people who may be or are victims of the accused or the offender; but</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is satisfied that there are no people who may be or are victims of the accused or the offender.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>On an application under subsection (1), the Tribunal must,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if satisfied that there are no people who may be or are victims of the accused or the offender, order that the Secretary is not required to give notice under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305273" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750044" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310184" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750044" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750044" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351454" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305274" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750045" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>21</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310185" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750045" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750045" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351454" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> but must pay to the accused or the offender promptly all money held in the account for the accused or the offender:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in every other case, order that the Secretary is required to give notice under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305275" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750046" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310186" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750046" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750046" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351454" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305276" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750047" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>21</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310187" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750047" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750047" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351454" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must comply with the order of the Tribunal.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (3) applies subject to the prior implementation of any provision of an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim requiring compensation to be withheld from the accused or the offender and used to satisfy outstanding fines of the accused or the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351455" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">27</label>
          <heading>Service of notices</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A notice or other document required by this Act to be served on, or given to, a person is sufficiently served if it is—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>delivered personally to the person; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>delivered to the person at the person’s usual or last known place of residence or business; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>sent by fax or email to the person’s fax number or email address; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>posted in a letter addressed to the person at the person’s usual or last known place of residence or business.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the person is absent from New Zealand, the notice or other document may be served on or given to the person’s agent in New Zealand.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the person is deceased, the notice or other document may be served on or given to the person’s personal representatives.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>A notice or other document sent to a person by post must, unless the contrary is shown, be treated as having been delivered to the person on the seventh day after the day on which it was posted; and in proving the delivery it is sufficient to prove that the letter was properly addressed and posted.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>Despite anything in subsections (1) to (4), a Tribunal may in any circumstances make an order directing the manner in which a notice or other document is to be served or given, or dispensing with the service or giving of the notice or document.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM351456" toc="yes">Procedure for making and determination of victims’ claims</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM351457" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">28</label>
          <heading>Filing of claims</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A victim’s claim may be filed by or on behalf of a person if—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice is given under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305279" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750050" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310190" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750050" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750050" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351457" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> notifying a payment into the account of money paid to the Crown in trust for an accused or an offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in the case where the money is required to be paid in trust for an accused, the accused is an offender (whether by reason of any earlier finding of guilt or entry of a plea of guilty in relation to an offence, or by reason of a finding of guilt or entry of a plea of guilty, after the giving of the notice under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305280" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750051" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310191" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750051" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750051" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351457" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> but before the filing of the person’s claim under this section, in relation to the offence charged); and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the person is a victim of the offender and has not obtained, and is not seeking, a judgment—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>in respect of the conduct on which the claim is based; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>in civil proceedings against the offender in a District Court or the High Court.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The claim must be—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in a form approved for the purpose by the Secretary; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>filed before the deadline specified in subsection (3).</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The deadline referred to in subsections (2), (4), and (5) is,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if the notice is, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305285" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 22" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750056" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 22</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310196" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750056" atidlm:targetKey="2110816" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351449" atidlm:targetName="prov 22" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750056" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351457" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, given as an addition to a previous notice, the later of the following:</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the close of the day that is 6 months after the sending date of the previous notice; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the close of the day that is 2 months after the sending date of the notice; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in every other case, the close of the day that is 6 months after the sending date of the notice.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may permit a victim’s claim to be filed within a further period it specifies if it is satisfied that the victim was prevented by factors beyond his or her control from filing the claim before the deadline.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal’s power under subsection (4) is exercisable on a written application for the purpose filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal before the deadline.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351458" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">29</label>
          <heading>No filing fees payable</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>No fee is payable to the Secretary of the Tribunal for filing a document relating to, or for the Tribunal hearing or determining, a victim’s claim filed under this subpart.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351459" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">30</label>
          <heading>Secretary of Tribunal to refer claims filed to Tribunal</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary of the Tribunal must, as soon as practicable after a claim or application is filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305287" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750058" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310198" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750058" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750058" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351459" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, refer the claim or application to the appropriate Tribunal to be dealt with in accordance with this subpart.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The <def-term id="DLM1906702">appropriate Tribunal</def-term> is a Tribunal designated in writing by the Chief District Court Judge to deal with the group of victims’ claims (if any) arising from—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305288" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750059" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310200" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750059" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750059" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351459" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (the <def-term id="DLM351460">notice</def-term>); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice that, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305289" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 22" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750060" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 22</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310201" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750060" atidlm:targetKey="2110816" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351449" atidlm:targetName="prov 22" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750060" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351459" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, is given as an addition to the notice.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Chief District Court Judge may designate a Tribunal for 1 or more specified groups of claims, or 1 or more specified classes of groups of claims, filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305290" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750061" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310202" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750061" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750061" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351459" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Chief District Court Judge may designate another Tribunal to deal with some or all of a claim or application if the Tribunal to which it has been referred under this section is, because of exceptional circumstances, unable to deal with all or that part of the claim or application.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <text>However, the Chief District Court Judge must consult with the Judge Advocate General before designating a Tribunal under this section if a claim to which the designation relates involves an offender convicted by the Court Martial, or found guilty by a disciplinary officer, under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986640" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194818 - Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194857" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007841" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194857" atidlm:targetKey="2572255" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM401062" atidlm:targetName="Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194857" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM401062.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351459" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194836"><amended-provision>Section 30(5)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986641" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194819 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194858" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007842" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194858" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194858" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194836" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351461" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">31</label>
          <heading>Offender to be given copy of claim and reasonable opportunity to make written submission on it</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Before determining a victim’s claim, the Tribunal must—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>serve a copy of the claim on the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>give him or her a reasonable opportunity to make written submissions on the claim.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>A copy of the claim must be served on the offender as soon as practicable after it is filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305292" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750063" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310204" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750063" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750063" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351461" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Information that identifies, or that may lead to the identification of, the address of the place where the victim lives must be removed from the copy of the claim served on the offender unless, in the Tribunal’s opinion, that information is necessary to ensure that the offender is fully and fairly informed of the nature of the claim.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal gives the offender the reasonable opportunity required by subsection (1) by requiring his or her written submissions to be filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>within 60 days after the expiry of the periods specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305294" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 33" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750065" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 33(a)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310206" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750065" atidlm:targetKey="2110830" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351463" atidlm:targetName="prov 33" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750065" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351461" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>within a further period the Tribunal is satisfied, on an application for the purpose before the expiry of that 60-day period, is justified by exceptional circumstances.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>In determining under subsection (4)(b) whether it is satisfied a further period is justified by exceptional circumstances, the Tribunal must have regard to the number and complexity of the victims’ claims filed against the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must, as soon as practicable, serve on a victim a copy of all submissions filed by the offender and relating to that victim.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351462" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">32</label>
          <heading>Procedure if no claims filed</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>If, at the expiry of the periods specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305296" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 33" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750067" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 33(a)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310208" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750067" atidlm:targetKey="2110830" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351463" atidlm:targetName="prov 33" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750067" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351462" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, no claims have been filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305297" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750068" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310209" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750068" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750068" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351462" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the Secretary of the Tribunal must advise the Secretary of that fact; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the Secretary must pay to the accused or the offender promptly all amounts of money held in the account for the accused or the offender.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (1)(b) applies subject to the prior implementation of any provision of an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim requiring compensation to be withheld from the accused or the offender and used to satisfy the accused’s or the offender’s outstanding fines.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351463" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">33</label>
          <heading>Period to allow all claims, offender’s submissions, etc</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal cannot determine a victim’s claim filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305299" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750070" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310211" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750070" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750070" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351463" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> until—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the 6-month period in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305300" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750071" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310212" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750071" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750071" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351463" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, and any further periods allowed under section 28(4), have expired; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the offender has been given the reasonable opportunity to make written submissions referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305302" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 31" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750073" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 31</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310214" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750073" atidlm:targetKey="2110828" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351461" atidlm:targetName="prov 31" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750073" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351463" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any oral submissions the Tribunal has agreed to hear under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305303" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 38" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750074" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 38</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310215" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750074" atidlm:targetKey="2110860" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351469" atidlm:targetName="prov 38" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750074" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351463" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> have been heard.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351464" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">34</label>
          <heading>Claims determined on papers</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Unless the Tribunal determines under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305304" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 38" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750075" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 38</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310216" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750075" atidlm:targetKey="2110860" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351469" atidlm:targetName="prov 38" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750075" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351464" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> also to hear oral submissions from the parties to a victim’s claim,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>neither the parties nor their representatives may appear before the Tribunal; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the claim must be determined by the Tribunal on the basis of the written material before it.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Consideration of written material before the Tribunal may be undertaken in whatever manner it thinks fit.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351465" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">35</label>
          <heading>Access to relevant court documents or records</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>To help to determine a claim filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305305" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750076" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310217" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750076" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750076" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Tribunal may, by making a request for the purpose to the appropriate Registrar or to the Judge Advocate General, and without paying a fee, access or search, inspect, and take or be issued with copies of or extracts from, court documents or records that—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <text>relate to criminal proceedings, proceedings of a disciplinary officer under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986642" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194820 - Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194859" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007843" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194859" atidlm:targetKey="2572255" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM401062" atidlm:targetName="Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194859" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM401062.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, or proceedings of the Court Martial; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>are or may be relevant to the determination of the claim.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Those court documents or records include—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>criminal records kept under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305307" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 71" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750078" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 71</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310219" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750078" atidlm:targetKey="2038943" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM311813" atidlm:targetName="prov 71" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750078" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM311185.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Summary Proceedings Act 1957</citation>, including—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>a reserved decision entered in those records; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>a minute or memorandum of criminal proceedings in a District Court appointed for the exercise of criminal jurisdiction; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>documents referred to in the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305309" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Criminal Proceedings (Search of Court Records) Rules 1974" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750080" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Criminal Proceedings (Search of Court Records) Rules 1974</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310221" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750080" atidlm:targetKey="3137813" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM42040" atidlm:targetName="Criminal Proceedings (Search of Court Records) Rules 1974" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750080" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZReg/fragxyxz_DLM42040.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, including—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the register of persons committed for trial and sentence, the register commonly known as the Return of Prisoners Tried and Sentenced, and the indexes to those registers; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>a file, or part of a file, or document relating to a criminal proceeding; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>records of <insertwords>Court Martial</insertwords> proceedings delivered to, and kept in accordance with the directions of, the Judge Advocate General, under <insertwords><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986643" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194821 - prov 75" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194860" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 75</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007844" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194860" atidlm:targetKey="10141810" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002030" atidlm:targetName="prov 75" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194860" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002020.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Court Martial Act 2007</citation></insertwords>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <text>any documents or records (for example, a charge report) created in connection with, and retained after, the summary trial or disposal of a charge by a disciplinary officer under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986644" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194807 - Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194861" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007845" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194861" atidlm:targetKey="2572255" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM401062" atidlm:targetName="Armed Forces Discipline Act 1971" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194861" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM401062.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351465" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194837"><amended-provision>Section 35(1)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986645" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194822 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194862" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007846" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194862" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194862" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194837" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
              <history-note id="DLM2194838"><amended-provision>Section 35(2)(c)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986646" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194822 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194863" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007847" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194863" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194863" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194838" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
              <history-note id="DLM2194839"><amended-provision>Section 35(2)(d)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986647" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194801 - prov 81" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194864" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 81</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007848" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194864" atidlm:targetKey="10327843" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1034362" atidlm:targetName="prov 81" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194864" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1034319.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194839" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Armed Forces Discipline Amendment Act (No 2) 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 98).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351466" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">36</label>
          <heading>Access to records of <insertwords>Court Martial</insertwords> proceedings, etc, to help to determine victims’ claims</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section applies to a document or record specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305313" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750084" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35(2)(c) or (d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310225" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750084" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750084" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351466" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, requested under section 35(1), and that the Judge Advocate General considers, and has advised the Secretary, should not be disclosed for reasons of security.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must not access or search, inspect, and take or be issued with copies or extracts from, the document or record, and must not use it for the purpose in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305316" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750087" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35(1)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310228" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750087" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750087" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351466" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, except with the permission of, and in accordance with any conditions specified by, the Judge Advocate General.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must comply with, and take all reasonably practicable steps to ensure others comply with, conditions specified by the Judge Advocate General.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section overrides <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305317" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750088" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310229" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750088" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750088" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351466" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194840"><amended-provision>Section 36 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986648" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194822 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194865" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007849" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194865" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194865" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194840" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351467" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">37</label>
          <heading>Relevant findings in criminal proceedings or proceedings of <insertwords>Court Martial</insertwords> or officer to be evidence</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A finding of fact is conclusive evidence of the matters to which it relates for the purposes of the determination of a victim’s claim filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305318" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750089" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310230" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750089" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750089" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351467" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> if the finding—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is recorded in a court document or record referred to in, and accessed under, <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305319" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750090" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35(1)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310231" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750090" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750090" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351467" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>is, in the Tribunal’s opinion, relevant to the determination of the claim.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In this section, a <def-term id="DLM351468">finding of fact</def-term> means—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a fact agreed on by the prosecutor and the offender; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a fact, express or implied, that was essential to a plea of guilty or a finding of guilt; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a fact disclosed by evidence at the hearing or trial, accepted as proved, and recorded in a decision.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section does not affect rights of appeal under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305320" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 51" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750091" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 51</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310232" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750091" atidlm:targetKey="2110844" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351487" atidlm:targetName="prov 51" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750091" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351467" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM2194841"><amended-provision>Section 37 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 July 2009</amendment-date>, by <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1986649" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM2194822 - prov 87" atidlm:xmlId="DLM2194866" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 87</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="amending-provision" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="1007850" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM2194866" atidlm:targetKey="10142208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1002056" atidlm:targetName="prov 87" atidlm:sourceName="DLM2194866" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1002048.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM2194841" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the <amending-leg>Court Martial Act 2007</amending-leg> (2007 No 101).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351469" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">38</label>
          <heading>Tribunal may also hear submissions in exceptional cases</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may also hear oral submissions from the parties to a victim’s claim (or from their representatives) if satisfied that exceptional circumstances make that necessary in the interests of justice.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In determining whether to hear oral submissions, the Tribunal must consider—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the nature of the victim’s claim; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the complexity of the issues concerned; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the amount claimed; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>any other matters it considers relevant.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>If it agrees to hear oral submissions, the Tribunal must as soon as practicable—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>fix a time and place for the hearing; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>give all parties notice of the time and place fixed.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may alter the time and place fixed for the hearing, or adjourn it from time to time and from place to place.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351470" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">39</label>
          <heading>Power to require information, documents, or answers</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>If it considers it necessary or desirable for the determination of a victim’s claim filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305321" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750092" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310233" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750092" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750092" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351470" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Tribunal may, by written notice served on a person (for example, a party to the claim), require that person—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>to give the Tribunal any information or class of information, or to answer any questions, specified in the notice; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>to produce to the Tribunal, or to a person specified in the notice acting on the Tribunal’s behalf in accordance with the notice, any document or class of documents specified in the notice; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>to appear before the Tribunal, or before a person specified in the notice acting on the Tribunal’s behalf in accordance with the notice, at a time and place specified in the notice, and answer questions related to matters specified in the notice.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Information required by a notice under subsection (1)(a) must be given in writing and,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if given by a natural person, must be signed by the person; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if given by a body corporate, must be signed by an officer authorised to sign on behalf of the body corporate.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person on whom a written notice under subsection (1) is served, or who, in accordance with a notice of that kind, appears before the Tribunal or a person acting on its behalf to answer questions, has the same privileges and immunities as witnesses and counsel in courts of law.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section does not limit or affect an enactment, rule of law, or order or direction of a court or tribunal that prohibits or restricts—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the making available of information or documents sought by, or sought by questions asked under, a notice under subsection (1); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the manner in which information or documents of that kind may be made available.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every person commits an offence against this section, and is liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding $1,000, who, without reasonable excuse, fails to comply with a notice under subsection (1), or fails to answer a question asked under the notice.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351471" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">40</label>
          <heading>Power to maintain order at hearings, etc</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>For the purposes of dealing with the matters before it, a Tribunal has the powers of a District Court, in the exercise of its civil jurisdiction, in respect of citing parties and conducting and maintaining order at the hearings of the Tribunal.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351472" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">41</label>
          <heading>Power to restrict publication of proceedings, etc</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>If a victim’s claim is filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305326" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750097" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310238" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750097" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750097" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351472" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Tribunal may, if satisfied that it is desirable to do so, make or give 1 or more of the following orders or directions:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>an order forbidding publication of a report or account of the whole or a part of—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the evidence adduced:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the submissions made:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>a document, or information, filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal, or received by or on behalf of the Tribunal in connection with the claim:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>an order forbidding the publication of—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the name of a person, or a name or particulars likely to lead to the identification of that person:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the affairs of a person:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a direction forbidding inspection without the Tribunal’s leave of a document filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal, or received by or on behalf of the Tribunal in connection with the claim:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>an order excluding all or any persons other than the parties to the proceedings, a lawyer engaged in the proceedings, and an officer of the Tribunal, from the whole or a part of the proceedings.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In exercising a power under subsection (1), the Tribunal must have regard to—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the interests of every person affected (including, without limitation, the privacy of a victim); and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the public interest.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may make or give an order or direction under this section on its own initiative or on the application of a party to the proceedings.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every application to the Tribunal for an order or direction under this section may be heard in public or in chambers.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>An order or direction under subsection (1)(a) or (b) or (c)—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>may be made or given for a limited period or permanently; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if it is made or given for a limited period, may be renewed for a further period or periods by the Tribunal under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305331" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 42" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750102" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 42</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310244" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750102" atidlm:targetKey="2110864" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351473" atidlm:targetName="prov 42" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750102" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351472" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if it is made or given permanently, may be reviewed by the Tribunal at any time under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305332" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 42" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750103" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 42</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310245" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750103" atidlm:targetKey="2110864" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351473" atidlm:targetName="prov 42" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750103" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351472" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <cf>1997 No 92 <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305333" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 39" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750104" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>s 39</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310246" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750104" atidlm:targetKey="2269207" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM417790" atidlm:targetName="prov 39" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750104" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM417770.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351472" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation></cf>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351473" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">42</label>
          <heading>Application for renewal or review of order or direction under section 41</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>If an order or direction is made or given under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305335" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 41" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750106" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 41(1)(a) or (b) or (c)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310248" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750106" atidlm:targetKey="2110863" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351472" atidlm:targetName="prov 41" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750106" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351473" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, a person may at any time apply to the Tribunal—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>for a renewal of the order or direction, if the order or direction was made or given for a limited time; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>for a review of the order or direction, if the order or direction was made or given permanently.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>An application may be made under subsection (1) by a person who was a party to the proceedings in which the order or direction was made or given or by any other person.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>After considering an application under this section, the Tribunal may renew, revoke, vary, or continue the order or direction as the Tribunal thinks fit.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <cf>1997 No 92 <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305339" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 40" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750110" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>s 40</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310252" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750110" atidlm:targetKey="2269208" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM417791" atidlm:targetName="prov 40" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750110" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM417770.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351473" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation></cf>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351474" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">43</label>
          <heading>Contravention of orders or directions under section 41</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every person commits an offence who breaches an order or direction made or given under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305341" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 41" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750112" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 41(1)(a) or (b) or (c) or (d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310254" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750112" atidlm:targetKey="2110863" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351472" atidlm:targetName="prov 41" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750112" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351474" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or evades or attempts to evade the order or direction.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every person who commits an offence against subsection (1) is liable on summary conviction,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in the case of an individual, to a fine not exceeding $1,000:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in the case of a body corporate, to a fine not exceeding $5,000.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <cf>1997 No 92 <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305346" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 41" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750117" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>s 41</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310259" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750117" atidlm:targetKey="2269209" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM417792" atidlm:targetName="prov 41" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750117" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM417770.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351474" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation></cf>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351475" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">44</label>
          <heading>Availability of documents filed in connection with claims</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The availability of documents filed with the Secretary of the Tribunal, filed in the Tribunal, or accessed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305347" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 35" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750118" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 35</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310260" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750118" atidlm:targetKey="2110832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351465" atidlm:targetName="prov 35" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750118" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351475" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> by the Tribunal, in connection with a victim’s claim under this subpart must be determined in accordance with the rules regulating the practice and procedure of District Courts.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>For the purposes of this section, a direction given by the Tribunal forbidding inspection of a document without the Tribunal’s leave must be treated as if it were given by, and required the leave of, a District Court Judge.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Nothing in this section applies to a document or record to which <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305348" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 31" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750119" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 31(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310261" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750119" atidlm:targetKey="2110828" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351461" atidlm:targetName="prov 31" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750119" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351475" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> or <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305349" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 36" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750120" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 36</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310262" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750120" atidlm:targetKey="2110800" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351466" atidlm:targetName="prov 36" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750120" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351475" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> applies.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351476" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">45</label>
          <heading>Other aspects of procedure</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>Subject to <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305350" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750121" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 28 to 44</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310263" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750121" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750121" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351476" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link>, <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305351" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750122" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310264" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750122" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750122" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351476" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link>, <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305352" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 59" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750123" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>59</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310265" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750123" atidlm:targetKey="2110854" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351497" atidlm:targetName="prov 59" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750123" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351476" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link>, and <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305353" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 60" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750124" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>60</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310266" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750124" atidlm:targetKey="2110855" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351498" atidlm:targetName="prov 60" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750124" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351476" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the Tribunal may regulate the procedure for determining victims’ claims in any manner it thinks fit.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351477" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">46</label>
          <heading>Tribunal to determine group of claims received</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must determine together as a group victims’ claims (including related questions as to interest and costs) filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305354" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750125" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310267" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750125" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750125" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351477" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> in response to—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305355" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750126" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310268" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750126" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750126" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351477" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (the <def-term id="DLM351478">notice</def-term>); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>a notice that, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305356" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 22" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750127" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 22</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310269" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750127" atidlm:targetKey="2110816" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351449" atidlm:targetName="prov 22" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750127" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351477" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, is given as an addition to the notice.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must not accept a victim’s claim unless satisfied, on the balance of probabilities, that—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the claimant is a victim of the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the victim has, through or by means of the offence, suffered injury, loss, or damage for which the victim has not received, and is not to receive, effective redress; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the claim discloses a cause of action that is, under the general law, one for which damages are, in the particular case, payable.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the Tribunal accepts a victim’s claim it may, after having had regard to all other related claims accepted by it, order that an amount of money must be paid to the victim concerned.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may also order that an amount of money must be paid to the victims concerned if the payment proposed is—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>agreed to by all victims and the offender concerned; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>one that the Tribunal considers is reasonable by way of final settlement of the victims’ claims concerned.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal’s determination of a group of claims filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305357" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750128" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310270" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750128" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750128" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351477" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> must be recorded in a single written order that specifies the entitlements (if any) of all victims concerned.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351479" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">47</label>
          <heading>Further provisions on determination of claims received</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal must determine any amounts to be paid to victims without taking account in any way of the amount of money actually held in the account for the offender.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In determining whether to order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305358" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750129" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46(3) or (4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310271" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750129" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750129" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351479" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> that an amount be paid to a victim by way of damages or exemplary damages, and in quantifying that amount, the Tribunal must apply the general law relating to the awarding of damages.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Tribunal may, if it thinks fit, include in the amount ordered to be paid to a victim under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305360" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750131" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46(3) or (4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310273" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750131" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750131" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351479" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> interest at a rate, not exceeding the prescribed rate, it thinks fit on some or all of the damages for all or a part of the period between the date when the cause of action arose and the date of the order.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>However, the Tribunal cannot give interest upon interest.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>In this section and in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305362" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 50" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750133" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 50</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310275" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750133" atidlm:targetKey="2110843" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351486" atidlm:targetName="prov 50" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750133" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351479" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, <def-term id="DLM351480">the prescribed rate</def-term> means the prescribed rate as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305363" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 62B" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750134" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 62B(4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310276" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750134" atidlm:targetKey="1675641" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM243748" atidlm:targetName="prov 62B" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750134" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM243694.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351479" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the District Courts Act 1947</citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>Without limiting the Tribunal’s powers, the Tribunal may dismiss a victim’s claim if satisfied that it is frivolous, vexatious, or made solely for the purpose of delay.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351481" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">48</label>
          <heading>Implementation of order</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must implement promptly an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305365" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750136" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310278" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750136" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750136" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if, at the expiry of the 20-working-day period in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305366" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 51" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750137" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 51(3)(b)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310320" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750137" atidlm:targetKey="2110844" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351487" atidlm:targetName="prov 51" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750137" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (the <def-term id="DLM351482">period</def-term>), no appeals against the order (<def-term id="DLM351483">appeals</def-term>), or applications for further time for filing appeals (<def-term id="DLM351484">applications</def-term>), have been filed; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if every application filed within the period has been withdrawn, or has been finally determined and declined; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if, at the expiry of all further time allowed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305367" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 51" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750138" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 51(3)(b)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310321" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750138" atidlm:targetKey="2110844" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351487" atidlm:targetName="prov 51" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750138" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> in response to applications filed within the period, no appeals have been filed; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>once all appeals filed within the period, or filed within further time allowed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305368" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 51" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750139" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 51(3)(b)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310322" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750139" atidlm:targetKey="2110844" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351487" atidlm:targetName="prov 51" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750139" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> in response to an application within the period, have been withdrawn or finally determined.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>However, if an application has been filed after the expiry of the period, the Secretary may defer implementing the order until any resulting appeal is withdrawn or finally determined.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the amounts to be paid under the order are, in total, equal to or less than the amount of money held in the account for the offender, the Secretary must implement the order fully by paying from the money held in the account for the offender the amounts to be paid under the order to the victims concerned.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the amounts to be paid under the order are, in total, more than the amount of money held in the account for the offender, the Secretary must implement the order in part by paying the money held in the account for the offender to the victims concerned on a proportional basis by reference to the amounts to be paid under the order to each of those victims.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>Implementation of an order in part, under subsection (4), does not prevent any or all of the victims concerned from enforcing their entitlements under the order against the offender, and the partially implemented order may be enforced—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>by way of a deduction, under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305370" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 18" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750141" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 18(1)(c)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310324" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750141" atidlm:targetKey="2110811" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351440" atidlm:targetName="prov 18" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750141" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, from any money received later under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305371" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 17" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750142" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 17</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310325" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750142" atidlm:targetKey="2110806" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351436" atidlm:targetName="prov 17" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750142" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>under subsection (6), as if it were a judgment of the District Court.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
              <para>
                <text>A copy of a partially implemented order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305373" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750144" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310327" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750144" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750144" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305374" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 50" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750145" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 50(3)(b)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310328" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750145" atidlm:targetKey="2110843" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351486" atidlm:targetName="prov 50" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750145" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351481" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> may be filed without fee in an office of a District Court for the purposes of enforcement and, on being so filed, the copy of the order has the same effect as a judgment of the District Court, and may be enforced accordingly.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351485" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">49</label>
          <heading>Procedure if victim or others entitled cannot be found</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must pay the money to the offender promptly if the Secretary is, 1 year after first being required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305375" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 48" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750146" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 48(3) or (4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310329" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750146" atidlm:targetKey="2110841" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351481" atidlm:targetName="prov 48" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750146" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351485" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> to pay to a victim money held in the account for the offender, unable, despite having taken reasonable steps for the purpose, to locate the victim or to identify and locate another person legally entitled to the money.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (1) applies subject to the prior implementation of any provision of an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim requiring compensation to be withheld from an offender and used to satisfy the offender’s outstanding fines.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section overrides <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305378" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 48" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750149" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 48</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310332" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750149" atidlm:targetKey="2110841" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351481" atidlm:targetName="prov 48" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750149" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351485" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351486" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">50</label>
          <heading>Order under section 46 must be varied in certain circumstances</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section applies if, after an order is made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305380" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750151" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310334" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750151" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750151" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351486" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the conviction of the offender to which the order relates is set aside—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>without an order for retrial; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>with a retrial being ordered but the retrial—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>is not proceeded with; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>does not result in a conviction; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>is ended by a stay of proceedings.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>If this section applies, the person whose conviction was set aside may file with the Tribunal any court record or other official document that records any or all of the matters referred to in subsection (1).</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>If the Tribunal is satisfied, on receiving any record or other official document under subsection (2), that this section applies, the Tribunal must—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>vary the relevant order made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305383" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750154" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310337" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750154" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750154" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351486" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> to exclude its application in respect of the conviction that has been set aside; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>if any money has been paid to a victim under that order, order that that money be repaid to the person whose conviction was set aside, together with interest on that sum at the prescribed rate.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351487" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">51</label>
          <heading>Appeal to High Court</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A party to a claim determined under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305384" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750155" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310338" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750155" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750155" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351487" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> may appeal to the High Court against the order concerned only on a question of law.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>However, no party may appeal against an order made by the Tribunal with the agreement of all parties under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305385" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750156" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46(4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310339" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750156" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750156" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351487" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>An appeal must be—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>brought by way of notice of appeal in accordance with rules of court; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>filed within 20 working days after notice of the decision or order is communicated to the appellant, or within any further time a High Court Judge allows on application made before or after the period expires.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>On any appeal under this section, the High Court may—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>make any determination or determinations it thinks should have been made:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>direct the Tribunal to—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>consider or determine (whether for the first time or again) any matters the High Court directs; or</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>rehear the proceeding:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>make any order or further order it thinks fit.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The relevant order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305386" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750157" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310340" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750157" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750157" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351487" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is suspended until an appeal under this section is withdrawn or finally determined.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351488" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">52</label>
          <heading>Release of surplus money to offender</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must pay to the offender promptly any amount of money that continues to be held in the account for the offender after an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305387" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750158" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310341" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750158" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750158" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351488" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> has been implemented fully under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305388" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 48" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750159" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 48(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310342" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750159" atidlm:targetKey="2110841" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351481" atidlm:targetName="prov 48" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750159" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351488" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subsection (1) applies subject to the prior implementation of any provision of an out-of-court final settlement of a specified claim requiring compensation to be withheld from an offender and used to satisfy the offender’s outstanding fines.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351489" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">53</label>
          <heading>End of process to be notified publicly in certain cases</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must, by notice in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>, notify publicly the fact that the procedure contemplated by this subpart in respect of a particular sum of money has concluded if the Secretary—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>paid the money into the account under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305390" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 18" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750161" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 18(1)(d)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310344" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750161" atidlm:targetKey="2110811" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351440" atidlm:targetName="prov 18" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750161" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>gave the notice of the payment of the money required by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305391" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 20" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750162" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 20</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310345" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750162" atidlm:targetKey="2110814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351447" atidlm:targetName="prov 20" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750162" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> using a method in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305392" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 21" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750163" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 21(4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310346" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750163" atidlm:targetKey="2110815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351448" atidlm:targetName="prov 21" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750163" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>has, under a section specified in subsection (2), paid out all or the last of the money.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The sections referred to in subsection (1)(c) are—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305395" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 32" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750166" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 32</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310349" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750166" atidlm:targetKey="2110829" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351462" atidlm:targetName="prov 32" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750166" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (procedure if no claims filed); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305396" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 48" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750167" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 48(3) or (4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310350" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750167" atidlm:targetKey="2110841" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351481" atidlm:targetName="prov 48" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750167" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (implementation of order); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305398" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 49" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750169" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 49(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310352" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750169" atidlm:targetKey="2110842" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351485" atidlm:targetName="prov 49" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750169" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (procedure if victim or others entitled cannot be found); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305400" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 52" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750170" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 52</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310353" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750170" atidlm:targetKey="2110845" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351488" atidlm:targetName="prov 52" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750170" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (release of surplus money to offender); or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                  <para>
                    <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305401" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 56" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750171" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 56</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310354" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750171" atidlm:targetKey="2110850" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351493" atidlm:targetName="prov 56" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750171" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351489" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> (procedure if offender or others entitled cannot be found).</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The notice in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis> required by subsection (1) must identify the sum of money by reference only to the notice referred to in subsection (1)(b).</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>A copy of every notice required by subsection (1) must be sent by the Secretary to the chief executive of each government department that the Secretary believes may have an interest in the matter.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM351490" toc="yes">Victims’ claims trust bank account</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM351491" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">54</label>
          <heading>Secretary must establish account</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must, for the purposes of this subpart, establish at a bank a victims’ claims trust bank account.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The bank must be a registered bank as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305405" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 2" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750175" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 2(1)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310358" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750175" atidlm:targetKey="1079884" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM199370" atidlm:targetName="prov 2" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750175" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM199363.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351491" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Reserve Bank of New Zealand Act 1989</citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The bank at which the account is established—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>must pay, for any month, interest on the sums held in the account at the same rate as that bank pays on money deposited for that month, at call, in an interest-bearing deposit account with that bank; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>may, with the Secretary’s agreement, retain for its own use, instead of all banking charges and fees otherwise payable to it in respect of the account, some or all of the interest payable by it on the account; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>must pay into the account, for the benefit of the relevant accused or offender, any interest payable by it on the account and that is not retained under paragraph (b).</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The arrangement in subsection (3)(a) is the only permitted and required investment of the money in the account.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
              <para>
                <text>The account must be audited by a chartered accountant (within the meaning of <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305409" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 19" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750179" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 19</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310363" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750179" atidlm:targetKey="2080601" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM391422" atidlm:targetName="prov 19" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750179" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM391420.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351491" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of New Zealand Act 1996</citation>) at the times and in the manner (if any) prescribed by regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305411" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750181" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310365" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750181" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750181" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351491" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351492" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">55</label>
          <heading>Payments from, and other operation of, account</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>The Secretary must ensure that money is paid out of the account, and that the account is otherwise operated, only as permitted or required by this subpart or by regulations made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305412" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 57" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750182" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 57</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310366" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750182" atidlm:targetKey="2110851" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351494" atidlm:targetName="prov 57" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750182" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351492" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351493" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">56</label>
          <heading>Procedure if offender or others entitled cannot be found</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>This subsection applies to money if, 1 year (or a longer period the Minister of Finance directs) after first being required by this subpart to pay the money to an accused or an offender, the Secretary is unable, despite having taken reasonable steps for the purpose, to locate the accused or the offender or to identify and locate another person legally entitled to the money.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Money to which subsection (1) applies—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>must, along with interest (if any) added to it under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305414" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 54" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750184" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 54(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310368" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750184" atidlm:targetKey="2110848" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351491" atidlm:targetName="prov 54" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750184" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351493" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, be treated as public money; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>must be transferred to the Crown Bank Account.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Money must be paid to a person out of the Crown Bank Account without further appropriation than this section if—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the money is required by this section to be treated as public money; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the person claims the money and establishes that claim to the satisfaction of the Treasury.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <cf>1989 No 44 <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305415" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 70" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750185" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>s 70</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310369" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750185" atidlm:targetKey="889806" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM162987" atidlm:targetName="prov 70" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750185" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM162980.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351493" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation></cf>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351494" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">57</label>
          <heading>Regulations on operation and auditing of account</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>The Governor-General may, by Order in Council, make regulations for all or any of the following purposes:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>providing for the circumstances and manner in which money may or must be paid out of the account:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>providing for the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, the Secretary may or must otherwise operate the account:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>providing for the manner and timing of the auditing of the account.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM351495" toc="yes">Victims’ Special Claims Tribunals</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM351496" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">58</label>
          <heading>Tribunals</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every Victims’ Special Claims Tribunal consists of a District Court Judge designated for the purpose of this subpart by the Chief District Court Judge.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Judge must be designated from a panel of District Court Judges maintained by the Chief District Court Judge.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>The Chief District Court Judge may at any time add or remove a Judge from the panel.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>The function of a Tribunal is to determine, in accordance with this subpart, victims’ claims filed under this subpart.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351497" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">59</label>
          <heading>Evidence</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>A Tribunal may receive as evidence any statement, document, information, or matter that, in the Tribunal’s opinion, may help the Tribunal to determine a victim’s claim, whether or not it would be admissible in a court of law.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351498" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">60</label>
          <heading>Decisions to be given in writing</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every decision of a Tribunal, and the reasons for the decision, must be recorded in writing, and a copy (together with a copy of any related order or direction) must, if practicable, be given promptly to—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the victims concerned; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the accused or the offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the Secretary.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>This section does not limit a Tribunal’s duty under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305416" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 46" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750186" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 46</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310370" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750186" atidlm:targetKey="2110835" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351477" atidlm:targetName="prov 46" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750186" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351498" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> to record in a single written order its determination of a group of victims’ claims filed under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305417" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 28" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750187" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 28</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310371" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750187" atidlm:targetKey="2110824" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351457" atidlm:targetName="prov 28" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750187" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351434.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351498" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351499" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">61</label>
          <heading>Proceedings of Tribunal not invalid for want of form</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>Proceedings before a Tribunal must not be held invalid for want of form.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351700" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">62</label>
          <heading>Services for Tribunal</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
              <para>
                <text>The Ministry of Justice must provide any secretarial, recording, and clerical services necessary to enable a Tribunal to discharge its function.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
      <subpart id="DLM351701" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" toc="yes" act.no="74" act.type="public" date.as.at="2009-07-01" date.assent="2005-06-03" date.first.valid="2005-06-04" stage="reprint" year="2005">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
        <heading>Suspension of limitation periods for certain claims by victims</heading>
        <prov id="DLM351702" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">63</label>
          <heading>Application</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>This subpart applies to every applicable limitation period for an action that is based on a claim—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>made by or on behalf of a victim; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>made against an offender; and</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>based on acts done or omitted to be done (whether before or after the commencement of this Act) by the offender in committing the offence.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>This subpart applies whether or not the action was—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>commenced before the commencement of this Act; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>one in respect of which a limitation defence (under the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305418" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="Limitation Act 1950" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750188" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Limitation Act 1950</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="leg-title" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310372" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750188" atidlm:targetKey="1787832" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM262436" atidlm:targetName="Limitation Act 1950" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750188" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM262436.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351701.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351702" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or any other law of New Zealand) could, before the commencement of this Act, have been pleaded successfully.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>However, nothing in this subpart affects—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>an action or arbitration determined before the commencement of this Act; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>the title to any property which is the subject of an action or arbitration of that kind.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM351703" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">64</label>
          <heading>Limitation periods suspended</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>The limitation periods to which this subpart applies cease to run while the offender is serving a sentence of imprisonment in a penal institution, prison, or service prison.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>In this section, <def-term id="DLM351704">serving a sentence of imprisonment in a penal institution, prison, or service prison</def-term>—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>means serving in a penal institution, prison, or service prison—</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>the sentence of imprisonment for the offence (as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305419" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 5" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750189" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 5(1)(a)(ii)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310373" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750189" atidlm:targetKey="2108657" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM351401" atidlm:targetName="prov 5" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750189" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM350826.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351701.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351703" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>); and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>any earlier sentence of imprisonment on which the sentence of imprisonment for the offence is directed to be served cumulatively; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>any later sentence that is directed to be served cumulatively on the sentence of imprisonment for the offence; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>includes spending time in a penal institution or a prison following a related recall application (as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305420" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 59" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750190" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 59</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310374" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750190" atidlm:targetKey="781144" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM138879" atidlm:targetName="prov 59" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750190" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM138435.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351701.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351703" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of the Parole Act 2002</citation>), but only if a final recall order (as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="305422" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 4" atidlm:xmlId="DLM750192" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 4(1)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="310376" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM750192" atidlm:targetKey="776602" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM137641" atidlm:targetName="prov 4" atidlm:sourceName="DLM750192" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM137639.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM351701.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM351703" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> of that Act</citation>) is made following the recall application.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
    </part>
